text: Aglaia brassii is a species of plant in the family Meliaceae. It is found in Australia, West Papua (Indonesia), Papua New Guinea, and the Solomon Islands. ==References== brassii Category:Sapindales of Australia Category:Flora of Western New Guinea Category:Flora of Papua New Guinea Category:Flora of the Solomon Islands (archipelago) Category:Vulnerable flora of Australia Category:Nature Conservation Act rare biota Category:Vulnerable biota of Queensland Category:Rare flora of Australia Category:Flora of Queensland Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot
